nodes.name: withdrawFromMoneyMarket

params._cTokenAddress: The Compound cToken contract address that will receive the tokens transferred
params._tokenAddress: The token contract addressthat will initiate the transfer

params._adminAddress1: The Lender admin wallet that will receive user fees and can call this contract's functions
params._adminAddress2: The Lender admim wallet that can call this contract's functions. All other admin addresses are identical to this

params._cTokenAddress: The address of the Compound cToken contract that will receive the tokens transferred
params._tokenAddress: The address of the token this contract has and wants to supply

params._amountOfUnderlyingToWithdraw: The requested amount of the given token to withdraw from the money market
params._cTokenAddress: The cToken contract address corresponding to the requested token
params._tokenAddress: The address of the token the user is requesting
params._cTokensRequested: The requested amount to withdraw from the money market denominated in cTokens

approveCTokenContract(address,address).notice: -------------- Approve --------------- ///Approves the token contract to send a large amount of tokens to the cToken contract

methods.constructor: The constructor's purpose is to define the user address that will receive funds when the withdrawl function is called as well as specifiying the admin accounts that have permission to call this contract's functions on the user's behalf, all done here so it is immutible from the point of contract creation

supplyToMoneyMarket(address,address).notice: Supplies the entirety of this contract's token balance to Compound's money market contracts and adds the amount supplied to the princapalHolder in state

withdrawFromMoneyMarket(address,address,.notice: Withdraws a specified amount from Compound's money market contracts to this contract, subtracts the amount of principal being withdrawn from the principal holder in state, transfers 9.5% of interest earned fee to the Lender admin wallet, then transfers the user the remaining contract balance

userdoc.notice: The contract is intended to be used as a user contract wallet that will allow users to easily interact with Compound's money market contracts through the Lender UI
